.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE-LIST 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource\-list \- List live Grafana datasource inventory.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource list [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
List live Grafana datasource inventory.
.PP
Use this when you need a non\-interactive inventory of datasources, either for the current org, one explicit org, or across all visible orgs.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-org\-id
list one explicit Grafana org.
.TP
.B \-\-all\-orgs
aggregate datasource inventory across visible orgs. Requires Basic auth.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format, \-\-text, \-\-table, \-\-csv, \-\-json, \-\-yaml
output mode controls.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-columns
choose the displayed columns.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-header
suppress table headers.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
List live Grafana datasource inventory.
.EX
grafana-util datasource list --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --output-format text
.EE
.PP
List live Grafana datasource inventory.
.EX
grafana-util datasource list --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --all-orgs --output-format yaml
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-datasource\fR(1)
